attributes.Long form description: The instructor asks the student to disassemble the furniture.The student turns the furniture to unscrew the wheels one by one from the base frame, done this turns again the furniture so he can start to disassemble the trays of the side bars. Unscrews the hexagon cap nut of the side bars as well as the brackets, removes the top tray and continues screwing hexagon cap nut and screw of the middle tray of the furniture and places the middle tray together with the top tray. Repeats the previous steps for the bottom tray and stacks them together. Start disassembling the sidebar structure, and unscrewing the screws and the sidebars from the base frame. Once disassembled, place them together with the other trays. Disassemble the base frame structure, place them together with the trays and sidebar, and stops the recording.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews four wheels on the rolling cart.
The student disassembles the top tray of the rolling cart.
The student disassembles the middle tray of the rolling cart.
The student disassembles the lowest tray of the rolling cart.
The student unscrews the left pair of side bars on the rolling cart.
The student unscrews the right side bars of the rolling cart.
The student disassembles the base frame of the rolling cart.
